        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " upon the south, means \"throughout the whole country.\" The phrase is interesting, as showing that, in spite of the virtual independence of the tribes, and the general anarchy which prevailed during the time of the judges, there was nevertheless a feeling that they all formed one people. ",
